How duration of songs affects popularity for different genres

library(tidyverse)
genre=spotify$genre
ggplot(spotify, aes(x = duration_s, y = popularity,color=genre))  + geom_point()+
geom_smooth(method="lm", se = FALSE,color="black") +
facet_wrap(~genre,nrow=3)+xlab("Duration of songs in seconds")+ylab("Popularity of songs")

library(OneR)
## Warning: package 'OneR' was built under R version 3.5.3
library(viridis)
## Warning: package 'viridis' was built under R version 3.5.3
## Loading required package: viridisLite
## Warning: package 'viridisLite' was built under R version 3.5.2
mod1c=glm(popularity~duration_s*loudness,data=spotify)
mod1d=glm(popularity~duration_s+loudness,data=spotify)
anova(mod1c,mod1d,test="Chisq")
## Analysis of Deviance Table
## 
## Model 1: popularity ~ duration_s * loudness
## Model 2: popularity ~ duration_s + loudness
##   Resid. Df Resid. Dev Df Deviance Pr(>Chi)    
## 1      8503    1164335                         
## 2      8504    1170158 -1  -5822.2    7e-11 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
mod1=mod1c

loudness.level.df = expand.grid(loudness=seq(-16.809, 0.004 , 0.5), duration_s= seq( 84.36, 362.33 , 1))
loud.int.pred = predict(mod1, type = "response", newdata = loudness.level.df)
loud.int.pred.df = data.frame(loudness.level.df,mod1.prob=as.vector(loud.int.pred))

ggplot(loud.int.pred.df, aes(x = duration_s, y = mod1.prob,
group = loudness, color = loudness)) + geom_line()+xlab("Duration")+ylab("Popularity")+scale_color_viridis(option="B",name="Loudness")

## 0.02240 0.03470 0.04630 0.06427 0.07630 0.21700
mod3a=glm(popularity~duration_s*speechiness,data=spotify)
mod3b=glm(popularity~duration_s+speechiness,data=spotify)
anova(mod3a,mod3b,test="Chisq")
## Analysis of Deviance Table
## 
## Model 1: popularity ~ duration_s * speechiness
## Model 2: popularity ~ duration_s + speechiness
##   Resid. Df Resid. Dev Df Deviance Pr(>Chi)
## 1      8503    1209795                     
## 2      8504    1209957 -1  -162.13   0.2858
mod3=mod3a

speech.df = expand.grid(speechiness=seq(0.02240,0.21700,0.01),duration_s= seq( 84.36, 362.33 , 1))
speech.int.pred = predict(mod3a, type = "response", newdata = speech.df)
speech.int.pred.df = data.frame(speech.df,mod3.prob=as.vector(speech.int.pred))

group = speechiness, color = speechiness, se=TRUE)) + geom_line()+xlab("Duration")+ylab("Popularity")+labs(title="Interaction between Speechiness and Duration on Popularity")+scale_color_viridis(option="A",name="Speechiness")
